OL,3,CEx-councillor jailed for 20 weeks for
OL,4,Cstalking Dame Penny Mordaunt
OL,6,FBrandt, who worked as a professional
OL,7,Fsailor, was also sentenced for seven
OL,8,Fbreaches in December 2025 of a
OL,9,Fstalking protection order in place
OL,10,Funtil November 2034 by failing to
OL,11,Fnotify police of devices capable of
OL,12,Fconnecting to the internet and of the
OL,13,Fcreation of accounts on Facebook and
OL,14,FSnapchat.
OL,16,FHe was sentenced to 12 weeks in prison
OL,17,Ffor the stalking offence and eight
OL,18,Fweeks to serve consecutively for the
OL,19,Fbreaches.
