OL,6,FThe court also heard allegations of
OL,7,Finappropriate behaviour by Brandt
OL,8,Ftowards other women.
OL,10,FIn a victim impact statement read to
OL,11,Fthe court, the former Conservative
OL,12,FParty leadership candidate said that
OL,13,Fshe had been "living in fear" causing
OL,14,Fher to increase security at her office
OL,15,Fand at home, changing her routine.
OL,17,FShe was also given the protection of a
OL,18,Fplain-clothes policeman to "shadow"
OL,19,Fher at a carol service where she was
OL,20,Fthe special guest.
